    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jp.00226_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">St. Louis.</name><ptr target="loc.05991_n1"/>
                    <date when="1880-07-15">Feb. 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr Whitman</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                I received your book and
                photograph, I thank you very much
                indeed for both of them.
            </p>
            <p>
                I have enjoyed reading your book very much as it gave me a very different
                opinion of the private soldier, from
                that which I before possessed.
            </p>
            <p>
                I received your book some three weeks
                ago when I was preparing for my half
                yearly examinations and as I was very
                busy I could not get time to read it
                and I didn't want to write until
                I had done so.
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours affectionately</salute>
                <signed>William Mills</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jp.00225_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <!--Whitman wrote poetry on this page, and Traubel left a note - both unrelated to letter-->
        </body>
